Alhaji Isa Baba Buji, one of the delegates from Jigawa State for the special convention of the All Progressives Congress (APC), is dead. Daily Trust gathered Buji died in Abuja, on Tuesday. Until his sudden death, he was the APC vice chairman in charge of Jigawa South West. He reportedly slumped in the morning at the Jigawa State Liaison Office in Abuja while getting ready to go to the venue of the convention. Confirming the development, the Jigawa State APC Public Relations Officer, Bashir Kundu, told Daily Trust, “Of course, he died this morning”. The party spokesman explained that “He slumped at Jigawa State Liaison Office in Abuja but died while being rushed to the hospital. When we arrived at the hospital, he was confirmed dead.” Daily Trust gathered that the deceased was conveyed to the hospital by a member of the House of Representatives representing Birnin Kudu/Buji Federal Constituency, Engr. Magaji Da’u Aliyu. 